{"type":"message","id":"a308b2f4","parentId":"a2ed0125","timestamp":"2026-04-15T12:25:04.093Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The template uses `CONFLUENCE_BASE_URL`, `CONFLUENCE_API_TOKEN`, `CONFLUENCE_EMAIL` but the actual `openclaw.json` uses `CONF_BASE_URL`, `CONF_USERNAME`, `CONF_TOKEN`. There's a mismatch between the template variable names and what the actual MCP server expects.\n\nI need to also update the template configs to use the correct variable names, OR I need to make the script convert the names properly. The actual openclaw.json uses:\n- `CONF_BASE_URL`\n- `CONF_USERNAME`\n- `CONF_TOKEN`\n\nBut the template uses:\n- `CONFLUENCE_BASE_URL`\n\n\n- `CONFLUENCE_API_TOKEN`\n- `CONFLUENCE_EMAIL`\n\nSo I need to update all three team config templates to use the correct variable names that the MCP server actually expects.","thinkingSignature":"aae017c1f3d670b11d4fd070f75e12e162d72e2df4c071e8a7af1a706577eff0"},{"type":"text","text":"Template cЕ©ng sai tГЄn biбєїn (`CONFLUENCE_BASE_URL`, `CONFLUENCE_API_TOKEN`, `CONFLUENCE_EMAIL`) вЂ” khГґng khб»›p vб»›i biбєїn mГ  `confluence-mcp-server` thб»±c sб»± Д‘б»Ќc (`CONF_BASE_URL`, `CONF_USERNAME`, `CONF_TOKEN`). Fix cбєЈ template:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_wkkm0b6143l4_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"for f in /root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/ahv-openclaw-setup/configs/team-*.json; do\n  python3 -c \"\nimport json, sys\nwith open('$f') as fp:\n    d = json.load(fp)\nmcp = d.get('mcp', {})\nservers = mcp.get('servers', {})\nfor key in servers:\n    env = servers[key].get('env', {})\n    if 'CONFLUENCE_BASE_URL' in env:\n        env['CONF_BASE_URL'] = env.pop('CONFLUENCE_BASE_URL')\n    if 'CONFLUENCE_API_TOKEN' in env:\n        env['CONF_TOKEN'] = env.pop('CONFLUENCE_API_TOKEN')\n    if 'CONFLUENCE_EMAIL' in env:\n        env['CONF_USERNAME'] = env.pop('CONFLUENCE_EMAIL')\nwith open('$f', 'w') as fp:\n    json.dump(d, fp, indent=2)\nprin