{"type":"message","id":"89f6c579","parentId":"33a5ac8d","timestamp":"2026-04-15T12:26:16.413Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I see the real issue! The original file uses `mcpServers` (camelCase) as the top-level key, but the `applyCredentials` function looks for `config.mcp?.servers` (lowercase `mcp`). The Python script that \"fixed\" the config looked for `mcp.servers` (the lowercase version), but the actual key in the JSON is `mcpServers`.\n\nSo the `applyCredentials` function is checking `config.mcp?.servers` but the JSON has `config.mcpServers`, not `config.mcp.servers`!\n\nThis means the `applyCredentials` function was iterating over `config.mcp?.servers` which would be `undefined`, so it never actually applied any credentials. \n\nThe real problem is a case mismatch вЂ” the function needs to check `config.mcpServers?.servers` to match what's actually in the JSON structure. I see the issue nowвЂ”the setup script references `config.mcp?.servers` but the actual config has `config.mcpServers`, so the credentials are never being applied. I need to update the `applyCredentials` function to check both `mcpServers` and `mcp` keys to handle whatever structure the config ends up with after the path substitutions.","thinkingSignature":"13eaac59822ba2d918289bacd3768411a332364440934baa0af225863e225e2e"},{"type":"text","text":"PhГЎt hiб»‡n thГЄm bug nghiГЄm trб»Ќng! Config dГ№ng `mcpServers` (camelCase) nhЖ°ng script check `config.mcp?.servers` в†’ luГґn lГ  `undefined` в†’ credentials **khГґng bao giб»ќ Д‘Ж°б»Јc apply!\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_w6n93ji2nqeg_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review && git show HEAD:ahv-openclaw-setup/bin/ahv-setup.js | grep -n \"mcp?.servers\\|mcpServers\" | head -20"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":365,"output":398,"cacheRead":39449,"cacheWrite":615,"totalTokens":