{"type":"message","id":"10c70a05","parentId":"358e962c","timestamp":"2026-04-15T12:31:05.110Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Wait, the `bash -s dev` part doesn't pass `dev` as argument to install.sh. The install.sh reads `$1` which would be the first argument to install.sh, not to bash. Let me think...\n\nWhen you run:\n```\ncurl ... | bash -s dev\n```\nThen `bash` receives `dev` as its first argument, which becomes `$1` for install.sh. So `bash -s dev` would work.\n\nBut actually, a better approach:\n```\nbash -c \"$(curl -fsSL ...)\" dev\n```\nor\n```\ncurl ... | bash -s -- dev\n\n\n```\n\nWith the `--` separator, everything after it gets passed as positional arguments to install.sh, so `curl ... | bash -s -- dev` would correctly set `$1` to `dev`.\n\nWhen running `curl | bash -s dev`, the shell script receives `dev` as its first argument, which then gets passed to the ahv-setup.js call as the team parameter.\n\n```","thinkingSignature":"a98a28dcdcbdd08269ddb5cbbef848a21b209e53888b765b55846650153af3aa"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_3btys2bw468o_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review && git add ahv-openclaw-setup/ && git diff --cached --stat"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":171,"output":260,"cacheRead":52978,"cacheWrite":514,"totalTokens":53923,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776256257695,"responseId":"062eb802af3178555234fe7071f3d68c"}}
