{"type":"message","id":"bdd271e7","parentId":"1cf15870","timestamp":"2026-04-15T12:45:24.790Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants me to create a complete setup package for OpenClaw and push it to a separate branch. This should include:\n- Full skills\n- All 34 agents with their files\n- References\n- Everything needed for a new user to get started\n\nLet me think about what this means:\n1. The current setup package in `ahv-openclaw-setup/` exists but the user wants a more complete setup\n2. They want it pushed to a different branch (not main)\n3. It should include skills, agents, and references\n\nThe key insight here is: the current setup repo (github.com/maiychrus25/setup-openclaw) is what gets cloned when users run the install command. \n\nSo I need to structure the ahv-openclaw-setup directory with the shell script for installation, the Node.js setup logic, team configurations, and then copy over all the skill definitions and agent definitions from the v4-ecosystem-review workspace into this package so everything's self-contained and ready to go. I'll need to figure out the Git workflow for pushing this to a separate branch.\n\nThe core task is to build out a complete setup package with all skills, agents, configs, and dependencies included, then push it to a new branch for the team to use.\n\nThe setup repository already has the foundation with the install script, configuration templates, and a skills pack, but it's missing the actual agent definition files and the skills are encrypted rather than plain text. The core issue is that when cloning the repo to a different machine, those agent definition files won't be available locally, so the setup script can't find them. I need to figure out what files are actually missing from the repository versus what's in the backup, and then add those to the setup repo so the installation process works independently of any local files. I see the issue nowвЂ”the agent definitions exist in the repo but weren't being staged or committed properly. I need to commit the `agent-defs/` and `agent-templates/` directories from the setup repo, then push to a new branch like `feat/complete-setup`. The real challenge is that GitHub has file size limits for individual files (100MB) and repo sizes (10GB), so I need to either compress the skills.pack, keep it as a reference, or implement a download mechanism instead of committing large binary files directly.\n\nLet me check the actual size of skills.pack and other assets, then build out the complete setup by creating the missing directories and pushing everything to a feature branch. I need to structure the repo properly with all the agent definitions and documentation, then push it to a new branch with a clean git history so the team can clone and start using it immediately.","thinkingSignature":"d69edb311b4a43131ef10743e202899cce5d290d9dfd0e68fafe2f6466289351"},{"type":"text","text":"LГ m ngay. TГґi sбєЅ tбєЎo setup hoГ n chб»‰nh trГЄn branch `feat/complete-setup`.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_pl4lx1i4fz97_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/ahv-openclaw-setup && du -sh . && du -sh skills.pack && ls agent-defs/ | wc -l && ls agent-templates/ | wc -l"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_pl4lx1i4fz97_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/ahv-openclaw-setup && du -sh skills.pack bin/ agent-defs/ agent-templates/ configs/ README.md install.sh scripts/"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":0,"output":712,"cacheRead":78761,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":79473,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776257105139,"responseId":"062ebb52a707fe97ed4f28b6c6b1d05b"}}
