{"type":"message","id":"4803d5ce","parentId":"7f43dd9d","timestamp":"2026-04-15T12:52:20.665Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now the configs are restored to the correct setup repo format (`mcp.servers`). Now let me check what the script actually expects for the config format. The script uses:```jsconst mcpServers = config.mcpServers || config.mcp?.servers || {};```So it supports both `mcpServers` (workspace format) and `mcp.servers` (setup repo format). The committed configs use `mcp.servers` which is fine.\n\nBut wait - the committed configs have `CONF_BASE_URL` etc. or the old `CONFLUENCE_BASE_URL`? Let me check:","thinkingSignature":"53452bf72076e4ccb71ffcad8ddcabe062d30968e0f787d15f5badb60db1f80f"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_lyytf3ayfid4_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/ahv-openclaw-setup && python3 -c \"\nimport json\nfor f in ['configs/team-dev.json']:\n    d = json.load(open(f))\n    for k,v in d.get('mcp',{}).get('servers',{}).items():\n        if 'confluence' in k.lower():\n            print(k, v.get('env',{}))\n\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":194,"output":242,"cacheRead":164053,"cacheWrite":821,"totalTokens":165310,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776257533747,"responseId":"062ebcff664da61a46dd03eb4094293c"}}
