{"type":"message","id":"f6a6f699","parentId":"12d3dcd9","timestamp":"2026-04-16T01:41:59.986Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The encrypt function works for simple data but fails for all real files. This is very strange. Let me investigate why.\n\nThe issue is that Python's `zlib.compress` uses level=6 by default, which should always produce valid zlib data. But the round-trip test with the actual file failed...\n\nWait, I see! The `encrypt` function in the loop encrypts and then I try to decrypt inside the loop. But the encrypt function encrypts and returns base64. The issue might be that I'm computing the key bytes differently.\n\nLet me re-examine: Python bytes ^ key byte works fine. The test with simple data worked. But for ALL files it fails. This is suspicious.\n \nI'm wondering if the compression itself is producing invalid data, but zlib should always produce valid output. Let me trace through the encryption and decryption steps more carefully to see where the mismatch is happening. I'm realizing the compression itself might be introducing corruptionвЂ”the same algorithm works fine with simple test data but fails consistently across all 309 real files, which suggests the issue isn't with the encryption loop but rather with how zlib is handling the larger file content.\n\nLet me try bypassing compression entirely and just test with the raw XOR encryption to see if the problem is in the decompress step or somewhere else entirely.","thinkingSignature":"90da76dd60a04298af5054c5388980ffb9f9bc5cb6b53c60d5958ac094a1d8a7"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_by56rm19q2t3_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/ahv-openclaw-setup && python3 << 'PYEOF'\nimport os, json, zlib, base64\n\nAGENTS = ['agile-product-owner','clean-code','code-reviewer','coding-standards','content-strategy',\n  'database-reviewer','database-schema-designer','epic-design','harness-optimizer',\n  'market-intelligence','master-orchestrator','performance-optimizer','planner',\n  'playwright-pro','product-marketing-context','product-strategy','prompt-optimizer',\n  'realistic-seeder','refactor-cleaner','security-reviewer','senior-architect',\n  'senior-backend','senior-devops','senior-frontend','senior-qa','senior-security',\n  'seo-audit','shadcn-expert','stitch-design','stitch-loop','typescript-reviewer',\n  'ui-design-system','ui-ux-pro-max']\n\nSKILL_KEY = \"ahv-openclaw-2026\"\nSKILL_KEY_BYTES = SKILL_KEY.encode()\n\ndef encrypt(data_bytes):\n    out = bytearray(len(data_bytes))\n    for i in range(len(data_bytes)):\n        out[i] = data_bytes[i] ^ SKILL_KEY_BYTES[i % len(SKILL_KEY_BYTES)] ^ (i & 0xff)\n    compressed = zlib.compress(bytes(out))\n    return base64.b64encode(compressed).decode()\n\ndef decrypt(encrypted_b64):\n    buf = base64.b64decode(encrypted_b64)\n    dec = bytearray(len(buf))\n    for i in range(len(buf)):\n        dec[i] = buf[i] ^ SKILL_KEY_BYTES[i % len(SKILL_KEY_BYTES)] ^ (i & 0xff)\n    return zlib.decompress(bytes(dec))\n\nmanifest = []\npayloads = {}\nfailed = []\n\nfor agent in sorted(AGENTS):\n    src_dir = f'agent-defs/{agent}' if os.path.isdir(f'agent-defs/{agent}') else f'agent-templates/{agent}'\n    if not os.path.isdir(src_dir):\n        continue\n    for fname in sorted(os.listdir(src_dir)):\n        fpath = os.path.join(src_dir, fname)\n        if not os.path.isfile(fpath):\n            continue\n        with open(fpath, 'rb') as f:\n            content = f.read()\n        entry_path = f'{agent}/{fname}'\n        \n        # Test: skip compression, just XOR + base64\n        compressed = zlib.compress(bytes(content))\n        test_encrypted = base64.b64encode(compressed).decode()\n        \n        # Try decrypting plain compressed\n        try:\n            buf = base64.b64decode(test_encrypted)\n            dec = zlib.decompress(bytes(buf))\n            if dec != content:\n                failed.append((entry_path, 'plain compress mismatch'))\n        except Exception as e:\n            failed.append((entry_path, f'plain compress fail: {e}'))\n        \n        # Now test full encrypt\n        encrypted = encrypt(content)\n        try:\n            text = decrypt(encrypted)\n            if text != content:\n                failed.append((entry_path, 'encrypt mismatch'))\n        except Exception as e:\n            failed.append((entry_path, str(e)))\n        \n        manifest.append({'file': entry_path, 'size': len(content)})\n        payloads[entry_path] = encrypted\n\nprint(f'Generated {len(manifest)} entries')\nif failed:\n    print(f'FAILED ({len(failed)}):')\n    for f in failed[:3]:\n        print(f'  {f[0]}: {f[1]}')\nelse:\n    print('All OK!')\nPYEOF"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":3645,"output":1053,"cacheRead":19989,"cacheWrite":14607,"totalTokens":39294,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776303690102,"responseId":"062f714ba4893578ac66b156d59eabf3"}}
