{"type":"message","id":"980eba66","parentId":"d5684718","timestamp":"2026-04-16T01:43:00.960Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Interesting! Even Test 1 (AGENTS.md) fails here but succeeded in the previous standalone test. The difference must be in the `encrypt` function itself. Let me compare...\n\nIn the previous successful test:\n```python\nout = bytearray(len(compressed))\nfor i in range(len(compressed)):\n    out[i] = compressed[i] ^ SKILL_KEY_BYTES[i % len(SKILL_KEY_BYTES)] ^ (i & 0xff)\n```\n\nIn the `encrypt` function:\n```python\nout = bytearray(len(data_bytes))\nfor i in range(len(data_bytes)):\n    out[i] = data_bytes[i] ^ SKILL_KEY_BYTES[i % len(SKILL_KEY_BYTES)] ^ (i & 0xff)\n\n\n```\n\nAh, I see the bug now! The `encrypt` function is applying XOR to the wrong dataвЂ”it's XORing the original file content instead of the compressed bytes, which means the decompression step is trying to read XOR'd garbage instead of valid compressed data.\n\nI need to reverse the order: first compress the content, then XOR the compressed output, and base64 encode that result. When decrypting, I'll base64 decode, reverse the XOR with the same key, then decompress to recover the original content.","thinkingSignature":"17c649153af6f1f57c387881eee21ca5062d101d384bde07e15ea81b0c36beee"},{"type":"text","text":"Found the bug вЂ” `encrypt` applies XOR to wrong data (content instead of compressed bytes):\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_fl0bbijsjyry_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/ahv-openclaw-setup && python3 << 'PYEOF'\nimport os, json, zlib, base64\n\nAGENTS = ['agile-product-owner','clean-code','code-reviewer','coding-standards','content-strategy',\n  'database-reviewer','database-schema-designer','epic-design','harness-optimizer',\n  'market-intelligence','master-orchestrator','performance-optimizer','planner',\n  'playwright-pro','product-marketing-context','product-strategy','prompt-optimizer',\n  'realistic-seeder','refactor-cleaner','security-reviewer','senior-architect',\n  'senior-backend','senior-devops','senior-frontend','senior-qa','senior-security',\n  'seo-audit','shadcn-expert','stitch-design','stitch-loop','typescript-reviewer',\n  'ui-design-system','ui-ux-pro-max']\n\nSKILL_KEY = \"ahv-openclaw-2026\"\nSKILL_KEY_BYTES = SKILL_KEY.encode()\n\ndef encrypt(data_bytes):\n    # BUG WAS: XOR the content bytes directly\n    # FIX:    XOR the COMPRESSED bytes, not the content\n    compressed = zlib.compress(data_bytes)\n    out = bytearray(len(compressed))\n    for i in range(len(compressed)):\n        out[i] = compressed[i] ^ SKILL_KEY_BYTES[i % len(SKILL_KEY_BYTES)] ^ (i & 0xff)\n    return base64.b64encode(bytes(out)).decode()\n\ndef decrypt(encrypted_b64):\n    buf = base64.b64decode(encrypted_b64)\n    dec = bytearray(len(buf))\n    for i in range(len(buf)):\n        dec[i] = buf[i] ^ SKILL_KEY_BYTES[i % len(SKILL_KEY_BYTES)] ^ (i & 0xff)\n    return zlib.decompress(bytes(dec))\n\nmanifest = []\npayloads = {}\nfailed = []\n\nfor agent in sorted(AGENTS):\n    src_dir = f'agent-defs/{agent}' if os.path.isdir(f'agent-defs/{agent}') else f'agent-templates/{agent}'\n    if not os.path.isdir(src_dir):\n        continue\n    for fname in sorted(os.listdir(src_dir)):\n        fpath = os.path.join(src_dir, fname)\n        if not os.path.isfile(fpath):\n            continue\n        with open(fpath, 'rb') as f:\n            content = f.read()\n        entry_path = f'{agent}/{fname}'\n        encrypted = encrypt(content)\n        try:\n            text = decrypt(encrypted)\n            if text != content:\n                failed.append((entry_path, 'mismatch'))\n        except Exception as e:\n            failed.append((entry_path, str(e)))\n        manifest.append({'file': entry_path, 'size': len(content)})\n        payloads[entry_path] = encrypted\n\nprint(f'Generated {len(manifest)} entries')\nif failed:\n    print(f'FAILED ({len(failed)}):')\n    for f in failed[:5]:\n        print(f'  {f[0]}: {f[1]}')\nelse:\n    print('вњ… All 309 entries verified OK!')\n\npack = {\n    'version': '1.0',\n    'packedAt': '2026-04-16T00:00:00.000Z',\n    'fileCount': len(manifest),\n    'key': SKILL_KEY,\n    'manifest': manifest,\n    'payloads': payloads\n}\nwith open('skills.pack', 'w') as f:\n    json.dump(pack, f, indent=2)\nprint(f'вњ… Pack saved: {os.path.getsize(\"skills.pack\")/1024:.1f}KB, {len(manifest)} entries')\n\n# Verify pack loads correctly\nwith open('skills.pack', 'r') as f:\n    loaded = json.load(f)\nprint(f'Verify load: {len(loaded[\"manifest\"])} entries, first={loaded[\"manifest\"][0][\"file\"]}')\nPYEOF"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":254,"output":1147,"cacheRead":39255,"cacheWrite":2252,"totalTokens":42908,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776303763508,"responseId":"062f719444d6312f5694aae2355f4e48"}}
