{"type":"message","id":"d51b1d6a","parentId":"94370f2e","timestamp":"2026-04-16T01:52:47.316Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Interesting! The `git ls-remote` works, which means the SSH access works. But the raw GitHub URL returns 404. This is because the raw.githubusercontent.com requires the repo to be **public**. The repo might be private!\n\nBut wait - the push worked fine. That's because we used SSH for git operations. The raw.githubusercontent.com URL requires the repo to be public.\n\nSo the issue is: **the repo is private**. The user can't access `https://raw.githubusercontent.com/...` because it's a private repo.\n\nOptions:\n1. Make the repo public\n2. Use a different hosting approach for the install script (e.g., GitHub Gist, or host it elsewhere)\n\n\n3. Have users clone the repo first with SSH or HTTPS authentication before running the install script\n\nI need to clarify this with the user - the repo is private, so they'll need to either make it public, use gist.raw.github.org, or clone it first with proper credentials before running the install script.","thinkingSignature":"9e1c88e9c524bb4979e0b4eac38cfb1d351275615ad2ef176e13ec6a1c0c6403"},{"type":"text","text":"Repo **private** nГЄn `raw.githubusercontent.com` chбє·n 404. Cбє§n make public hoбє·c dГ№ng Gist.\n\nCГЎch nhanh nhбєҐt вЂ” tбєЎo Gist cho `install.sh`:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_fpaat4p5yx5y_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat /root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/ahv-openclaw-setup/install.sh | wc -l && echo \"---\" && head -3 /root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/ahv-openclaw-setup/install.sh"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":303,"output":335,"cacheRead":57944,"cacheWrite":255,"totalTokens":58837,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776304357323,"responseId":"062f73e60ed907e