{"type":"message","id":"5b638405","parentId":"3b0206f6","timestamp":"2026-04-16T01:54:38.799Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The `--yes` flag sets `skipIntro = true` and defaults to team \"dev\". But the credentials prompt still appears. Let me check what's happening at the credentials step:","thinkingSignature":"436d1caa891be18a6edff682187fce7d8779333e08ff6d21f5d178307119d313"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_bzmxy4bvuc1s_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"sed -n '408,460p' /root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/ahv-openclaw-setup/bin/ahv-setup.js"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":264,"output":96,"cacheRead":59161,"cacheWrite":947,"totalTokens":60468,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776304474055,"responseId":"062f745b79d0938117d969e11a92f7fc"}}
{"type":"message","id":"cc5211a3","parentId":"5b638405","timestamp":"2026-04-16T01:54:39.028Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_bzmxy4bvuc1s_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"const args = process.argv.slice(2);\n  let team = null, skipIntro = false;\n  for (const arg of args) {\n    if (arg === \"--team\" || arg === \"-t\") {\n      const idx = args.indexOf(arg);\n      team = args[idx + 1];\n    }\n    if (arg.startsWith(\"--team=\")) team = arg.replace(\"--team=\", \"\");\n    if (arg === \"--yes\" || arg === \"-y\") skipIntro = true;\n  }\n\n  checkPrereqs();\n\n  if (!team) {\n    if (skipIntro) { team = \"dev\"; }\n    else {\n      const { selected } = await inquirer.prompt([{\n        type: \"list\", name: \"selected\", message: chalk.cyan(\"Chon team:\"),\n        choices: [\n          { name: \"рџ‘Ёрџ’» Team Dev  вЂ” Backend, Frontend, DevOps\", value: \"dev\" },\n          { name: \"рџ“Љ Team BA   вЂ” Product Owner, Strategy, Epic Design\", value: \"ba\" },\n          { name: \"рџ§Є Team QA  вЂ” QA, Playwright, Security, Performance\", value: \"qa\" }\n        ]\n      }]);\n      team = selected;\n    }\n  }\n\n  if (!TEAMS[team]) { console.log(chalk.red(`\\nвќЊ Team khong hop le: ${team}\\n`)); process.exit(1); }\n\n  console.log(chalk.bold(`\\nв–¶ ${TEAMS[team].name} вЂ” ${TEAMS[team].desc}`));\n  console.log(chalk.dim(`   Agents: ${TEAMS[team].agents.length} | MCP: ${TEAMS[team].mcp.join(\", \")}\\n`));\n\n  if (!skipIntro) {\n    const { confirm } = await inquirer.prompt([{\n      type: \"confirm\", name: \"confirm\", message: chalk.cyan(\"Tiep tuc cai dat?\"), default: true\n    }]);\n    if (!confirm) { console.log(chalk.dim(\"\\nDa huy.\\n\")); process.exit(0); }\n  }\n\n  let config = loadTemplate(team);\n  console.log(chalk.bold(chalk.underline(\"\\nрџ”ђ Nhap credentials\\n\")));\n  const answers = await collectCredentials(team);\n  config = applyCredentials(config, answers);\n\n  console.log(chalk.bold(\"\\nрџ“¦ Tom tat:\\n\"));\n  console.log(`  ${chalk.green(\"вњ“\")} Team: ${TEAMS[team].name}`);\n  console.log(`  ${chalk.green(\"вњ“\")} Agents: ${TEAMS[team].agents.length}`);\n  console.log(`  ${chalk.green(\"вњ“\")} MCP: ${TEAMS[team].mcp.join(\", \")}`);\n\n  const { write } = await inquirer.prompt([{\n    type: \"confirm\", name: \"write\",\n    message: chalk.cyan(\"\\nGhi config vao ~/.openclaw/openclaw.json?\"), default: true"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":118,"aggregated":"const args = process.argv.slice(2);\n  let team = null, skipIntro = false;\n  for (const arg of args) {\n    if (arg === \"--team\" || arg === \"-t\") {\n      const idx = args.indexOf(arg);\n      team = args[idx + 1];\n    }\n    if (arg.startsWith(\"--team=\")) team = arg.replace(\"--team=\", \"\");\n    if (arg === \"--yes\" || arg === \"-y\") skipIntro = true;\n  }\n\n  checkPrereqs();\n\n  if (!team) {\n    if (skipIntro) { team = \"dev\"; }\n    else {\n      const { selected } = await inquirer.prompt([{\n        type: \"list\", name: \"selected\", message: chalk.cyan(\"Chon team:\"),\n        choices: [\n          { name: \"рџ‘Ёрџ’» Team Dev  вЂ” Backend, Frontend, DevOps\", value: \"dev\" },\n          { name: \"рџ“Љ Team BA   вЂ” Product Owner, Strategy, Epic Design\", value: \"ba\" },\n          { name: \"рџ§Є Team QA  вЂ” QA, Playwright, Security, Performance\", value: \"qa\" }\n        ]\n      }]);\n      team = selected;\n    }\n  }\n\n  if (!TEAMS[team]) { console.log(chalk.red(`\\nвќЊ Team khong hop le: ${team}\\n`)); process.exit(1); }\n\n  console.log(chalk.bold(`\\nв–¶ ${TEAMS[team].name} вЂ” ${TEAMS[team].desc}`));\n  console.log(chalk.dim(`   Agents: ${TEAMS[team].agents.length} | MCP: ${TEAMS[team].mcp.join(\", \")}\\n`));\n\n  if (!skipIntro) {\n    const { confirm } = await inquirer.prompt([{\n      type: \"confirm\", name: \"confirm\", message: chalk.cyan(\"Tiep tuc cai dat?\"), default: true\n    }]);\n    if (!confirm) { console.log(chalk.dim(\"\\nDa huy.\\n\")); process.exit(0); }\n  }\n\n  let config = loadTemplate(team);\n  console.log(chalk.bold(chalk.underline(\"\\nрџ”ђ Nhap credentials\\n\")));\n  const answers = await collectCredentials(team);\n  config = applyCredentials(config, answers);\n\n  console.log(chalk.bold(\"\\nрџ“¦ Tom tat:\\n\"));\n  console.log(`  ${chalk.green(\"вњ“\")} Team: ${TEAMS[team].name}`);\n  console.log(`  ${chalk.green(\"вњ“\")} Agents: ${TEAMS[team].agents.length}`);\n  console.log(`  ${chalk.green(\"вњ“\")} MCP: ${TEAMS[team].mcp.join(\", \")}`);\n\n  const { write } = await inquirer.prompt([{\n    type: \"confirm\", name: \"write\",\n    message: chalk.cyan(\"\\nGhi config vao ~/.openclaw/openclaw.json?\"), default: true","cwd":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776304478972}}
{"type":"message","id":"aac62302","parentId":"cc5211a3","timestamp":"2026-04-16T01:54:45.388Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Found the bug! The `--yes` flag skips the team selection and confirmation prompts, but `collectCredentials()` is ALWAYS called regardless of `skipIntro`. When running piped/non-TTY, there's no stdin to read, so `inquirer.prompt()` hangs or errors.\n\nThe fix: when `skipIntro=true`, read credentials from environment variables if set. Let me check what env vars the install.sh passes:","thinkingSignature":"90fc6165b941cdb5cc719e80d9030d13926cfed589edd3c8089b971004795bec"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ojb9ik0hv6o9_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"sed -n '85,105p' /root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/ahv-openclaw-setup/install.sh"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":768,"output":139,"cacheRead":59949,"cacheWrite":394,"totalTokens":61250,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776304479034,"responseId":"062f7460286d90bc177c67807ecb928c"}}
{"type":"message","id":"d12b9978","parentId":"aac62302","timestamp":"2026-04-16T01:54:45.552Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_ojb9ik0hv6o9_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Run setup\n  local team=\"${1:-dev}\"\n  step \"Chay setup cho team: $team...\"\n  # Auto-skip confirmations when running via pipe (stdin already consumed by curl)\n  local skipFlag=\"\"\n  if [ ! -t 0 ]; then\n    skipFlag=\"--yes\"\n    info \"Detected piped mode вЂ” auto-skipping prompts\"\n  fi\n  node bin/ahv-setup.js --team \"$team\" $skipFlag\n\n  # Done\n  local cfg=\"${HOME}/.openclaw/openclaw.json\"\n  echo \"\"\n  log \"Setup hoan tat!\"\n  echo \"\"\n  echo \"  Tiбєїp theo:\"\n  echo \"  ${CYAN}1.${RESET} Restart gateway:\"\n  echo \"     openclaw gateway restart\"\n  echo \"\""}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":52,"aggregated":"# Run setup\n  local team=\"${1:-dev}\"\n  step \"Chay setup cho team: $team...\"\n  # Auto-skip confirmations when running via pipe (stdin already consumed by curl)\n  local skipFlag=\"\"\n  if [ ! -t 0 ]; then\n    skipFlag=\"--yes\"\n    info \"Detected piped mode вЂ” auto-skipping prompts\"\n  fi\n  node bin/ahv-setup.js --team \"$team\" $skipFlag\n\n  # Done\n  local cfg=\"${HOME}/.openclaw/openclaw.json\"\n  echo \"\"\n  log \"Setup hoan tat!\"\n  echo \"\"\n  echo \"  Tiбєїp theo:\"\n  echo \"  ${CYAN}1.${RESET} Restart gateway:\"\n  echo \"     openclaw gateway restart\"\n  echo \"\"","cwd":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776304485504}}
{"type":"message","id":"b3df1beb","parentId":"d12b9978","timestamp":"2026-04-16T01:54:52.966Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The install.sh passes `--yes` but doesn't pass the API key from the environment. The `collectCredentials()` function needs to read from `AHVHOLDING_API_KEY` env var when `skipIntro=true`.\n\nLet me check the `collectCredentials` function to understand what it reads and add a skip when `skipIntro=true` and env vars are available.","thinkingSignature":"3b28920259575f31f4a0d1ff1c470b63281c2feb7e8fcbf871197f9ae1a8e3b1"},{"type":"text","text":"Bug: `--yes` skip team selection nhЖ°ng `collectCredentials()` vбє«n chбєЎy вЂ” khГґng cГі stdin trong pipe mode в†’ treo. Fix: Д‘б»Ќc credentials tб»« env vars khi `skipIntro=true`:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ng5ba2pskiu3_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"sed -n '150,240p' /root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/ahv-openclaw-setup/bin/ahv-setup.js"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":310,"output":186,"cacheRead":60242,"cacheWrite":883,"totalTokens":61621,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776304485562,"responseId":"062f74668489e97b2744ebaa78665e41"}}
{"type":"message","id":"38c864b0","parentId":"b3df1beb","timestamp":"2026-04-16T01:54:53.161Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_ng5ba2pskiu3_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"if (!fs.existsSync(p)) { console.log(chalk.red(`\\nвќЊ Config not found: ${p}`)); process.exit(1); }\n  return JSON.parse(fs.readFileSync(p, \"utf8\"));\n}\n\n// в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ Collect credentials в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ\nasync function collectCredentials(team) {\n  const required = REQUIRED_CREDS[team];\n  const questions = [];\n\n  for (const cred of required) {\n    switch (cred) {\n      case \"AHV_API_KEY\":\n        questions.push({ type: \"input\", name: \"ahvApiKey\",\n          message: chalk.cyan(\"AHV API Key (tu https://auto.ahvchat.com в†’ Account в†’ API Keys):\"),\n          validate: (v) => v.startsWith(\"sk-\") || \"Phai bat dau bang sk-\" });\n        break;\n      case \"GITLAB_TOKEN\":\n        questions.push({ type: \"input\", name: \"gitlabToken\",\n          message: chalk.cyan(\"GitLab Token (https://gitlab.com в†’ Settings в†’ Access Tokens):\"),\n          default: \"glpat-\" });\n        break;\n      case \"CONF_TOKEN\":\n        questions.push({ type: \"input\", name: \"confUrl\",\n          message: chalk.cyan(\"Confluence URL (VD: https://annoinfo.atlassian.net/wiki):\"),\n          default: \"https://annoinfo.atlassian.net/wiki\" });\n        questions.push({ type: \"input\", name: \"confEmail\",\n          message: chalk.cyan(\"Confluence Email (Atlassian login email):\"),\n          validate: (v) => v.includes(\"@\") || \"Email khong hop le\" });\n        questions.push({ type: \"input\", name: \"confToken\",\n          message: chalk.cyan(\"Confluence API Token (https://id.atlassian.com в†’ Security в†’ API Tokens):\") });\n        break;\n      case \"STITCH_API_KEY\":\n        questions.push({ type: \"input\", name: \"stitchKey\",\n          message: chalk.cyan(\"Stitch API Key (https://stitch.design в†’ Dashboard):\"),\n          validate: (v) => v.length > 5 || \"Token khong hop le\" });\n        break;\n      case \"TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN\":\n        questions.push({ type: \"input\", name: \"telegramBot\",\n          message: chalk.cyan(\"Telegram Bot Token (tu @BotFather, format: 123456:ABC...):\"),\n          validate: (v) => v.includes(\":\") || \"Bot token phai co dang xxx:yyy\" });\n        break;\n    }\n  }\n  questions.push({ type: \"input\", name: \"openclawPath\",\n    message: chalk.cyan(\"openclaw home (ENTER = ~/.openclaw):\"),\n    default: \"$HOME/.openclaw\" });\n\n  return inquirer.prompt(questions);\n}\n\n// в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ Apply credentials to config в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ\nfunction applyCredentials(config, answers) {\n  config.env.AHVHOLDING_API_KEY = answers.ahvApiKey;\n  config.models.providers.ahvholding.apiKey = answers.ahvApiKey;\n\n  if (answers.gitlabToken) {\n    config.env.GITLAB_TOKEN = answers.gitlabToken;\n    if (config.mcp?.servers?.gitlab?.env) {\n      config.mcp.servers.gitlab.env.GITLAB_URL = answers.gitlabUrl || \"https://gitlab.com\";\n      config.mcp.servers.gitlab.env.GITLAB_TOKEN = answers.gitlabToken;\n    }\n  }\n\n  if (answers.confUrl && config.mcp?.servers?.confluence?.env) {\n    config.mcp.servers.confluence.env.CONFLUENCE_URL   = answers.confUrl;\n    config.mcp.servers.confluence.env.CONFLUENCE_EMAIL = answers.confEmail;\n    config.mcp.servers.confluence.env.CONFLUENCE_TOKEN = answers.confToken;\n  }\n\n  if (answers.stitchKey && config.mcp?.servers?.stitch?.env) {\n    config.mcp.servers.stitch.env.STITCH_API_KEY = answers.stitchKey;\n  }\n\n  // Telegram Bot\n  const bots = config.channels?.telegram?.bots || {};\n  for (const key of Object.keys(bots)) {\n    if (bots[key].botToken === \"YOUR_TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN\" && answers.telegramBot) {\n      bots[key].botToken = answers.telegramBot;\n    }\n  }\n\n  return config;\n}\n\n// в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ Install MCP servers в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ\nfunction installMcpServers(team, homePath, config) {\n  const mcpServers = TEAMS[team].mcp;\n  if (!mcpServers || mcpServers.length === 0) return;\n\n  const setupMcpDir = path.join(PKG_DIR, \"mcp-servers\");\n  const mcpDestDir = path.join(homePath, \"mcp-servers\");"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":56,"aggregated":"if (!fs.existsSync(p)) { console.log(chalk.red(`\\nвќЊ Config not found: ${p}`)); process.exit(1); }\n  return JSON.parse(fs.readFileSync(p, \"utf8\"));\n}\n\n// в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ Collect credentials в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ\nasync function collectCredentials(team) {\n  const required = REQUIRED_CREDS[team];\n  const questions = [];\n\n  for (const cred of required) {\n    switch (cred) {\n      case \"AHV_API_KEY\":\n        questions.push({ type: \"input\", name: \"ahvApiKey\",\n          message: chalk.cyan(\"AHV API Key (tu https://auto.ahvchat.com в†’ Account в†’ API Keys):\"),\n          validate: (v) => v.startsWith(\"sk-\") || \"Phai bat dau bang sk-\" });\n        break;\n      case \"GITLAB_TOKEN\":\n        questions.push({ type: \"input\", name: \"gitlabToken\",\n          message: chalk.cyan(\"GitLab Token (https://gitlab.com в†’ Settings в†’ Access Tokens):\"),\n          default: \"glpat-\" });\n        break;\n      case \"CONF_TOKEN\":\n        questions.push({ type: \"input\", name: \"confUrl\",\n          message: chalk.cyan(\"Confluence URL (VD: https://annoinfo.atlassian.net/wiki):\"),\n          default: \"https://annoinfo.atlassian.net/wiki\" });\n        questions.push({ type: \"input\", name: \"confEmail\",\n          message: chalk.cyan(\"Confluence Email (Atlassian login email):\"),\n          validate: (v) => v.includes(\"@\") || \"Email khong hop le\" });\n        questions.push({ type: \"input\", name: \"confToken\",\n          message: chalk.cyan(\"Confluence API Token (https://id.atlassian.com в†’ Security в†’ API Tokens):\") });\n        break;\n      case \"STITCH_API_KEY\":\n        questions.push({ type: \"input\", name: \"stitchKey\",\n          message: chalk.cyan(\"Stitch API Key (https://stitch.design в†’ Dashboard):\"),\n          validate: (v) => v.length > 5 || \"Token khong hop le\" });\n        break;\n      case \"TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN\":\n        questions.push({ type: \"input\", name: \"telegramBot\",\n          message: chalk.cyan(\"Telegram Bot Token (tu @BotFather, format: 123456:ABC...):\"),\n          validate: (v) => v.includes(\":\") || \"Bot token phai co dang xxx:yyy\" });\n        break;\n    }\n  }\n  questions.push({ type: \"input\", name: \"openclawPath\",\n    message: chalk.cyan(\"openclaw home (ENTER = ~/.openclaw):\"),\n    default: \"$HOME/.openclaw\" });\n\n  return inquirer.prompt(questions);\n}\n\n// в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ Apply credentials to config в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ\nfunction applyCredentials(config, answers) {\n  config.env.AHVHOLDING_API_KEY = answers.ahvApiKey;\n  config.models.providers.ahvholding.apiKey = answers.ahvApiKey;\n\n  if (answers.gitlabToken) {\n    config.env.GITLAB_TOKEN = answers.gitlabToken;\n    if (config.mcp?.servers?.gitlab?.env) {\n      config.mcp.servers.gitlab.env.GITLAB_URL = answers.gitlabUrl || \"https://gitlab.com\";\n      config.mcp.servers.gitlab.env.GITLAB_TOKEN = answers.gitlabToken;\n    }\n  }\n\n  if (answers.confUrl && config.mcp?.servers?.confluence?.env) {\n    config.mcp.servers.confluence.env.CONFLUENCE_URL   = answers.confUrl;\n    config.mcp.servers.confluence.env.CONFLUENCE_EMAIL = answers.confEmail;\n    config.mcp.servers.confluence.env.CONFLUENCE_TOKEN = answers.confToken;\n  }\n\n  if (answers.stitchKey && config.mcp?.servers?.stitch?.env) {\n    config.mcp.servers.stitch.env.STITCH_API_KEY = answers.stitchKey;\n  }\n\n  // Telegram Bot\n  const bots = config.channels?.telegram?.bots || {};\n  for (const key of Object.keys(bots)) {\n    if (bots[key].botToken === \"YOUR_TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN\" && answers.telegramBot) {\n      bots[key].botToken = answers.telegramBot;\n    }\n  }\n\n  return config;\n}\n\n// в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ Install MCP servers в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ\nfunction installMcpServers(team, homePath, config) {\n  const mcpServers = TEAMS[team].mcp;\n  if (!mcpServers || mcpServers.length === 0) return;\n\n  const setupMcpDir = path.join(PKG_DIR, \"mcp-servers\");\n  const mcpDestDir = path.join(homePath, \"mcp-servers\");","cwd":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776304493091}}
{"type":"message","id":"8a81b9fc","parentId":"38c864b0","timestamp":"2026-04-16T01:55:07.562Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the full picture. The fix needs to:\n1. When `skipIntro=true`, check env vars for credentials\n2. For AHV_API_KEY specifically, read from `AHVHOLDING_API_KEY` env var (which is what the install.sh sets)\n3. If required credentials are missing in skip mode, show a clear error message instead of hanging\n\nAlso, the install.sh needs to pass the API key as an env var. Let me check if install.sh already exports `AHVHOLDING_API_KEY`:","thinkingSignature":"8f6ee1daea78f2565a6c986bdfbe8b40f7303f0f420d63d4c55b005354c051cf"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_yj1o9mvacuqg_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -n \"AHVHOLDING\\|AHV_API_KEY\\|export\" /root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/ahv-openclaw-setup/install.sh | head -15"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":1169,"output":176,"cacheRead":60981,"cacheWrite":515,"totalTokens":62841,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776304493167,"responseId":"062f746e93f610cae0a1061f10fe9bc8"}}
