{"type":"message","id":"2d9f36fb","parentId":"1f1367da","timestamp":"2026-04-16T01:55:15.874Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So the install.sh reads `$AHVHOLDING_API_KEY` from the environment and passes it to the ahv-setup.js through the same variable. The ahv-setup.js needs to use `process.env.AHVHOLDING_API_KEY` when `skipIntro=true`.\n\nLet me now fix both:\n1. `ahv-setup.js`: use env vars when `skipIntro=true`\n2. `install.sh`: ensure `AHVHOLDING_API_KEY` is exported and passed through\n\nFor install.sh - the key is already in `$AHVHOLDING_API_KEY` when the user sets it before running. The script echoes the key (masked), so it IS available in the environment. \n\nBut I need to verify that subshells in bash won't lose the variable, and check whether the credentials collection code references the right environment variable name. There's also a mismatch between the variable names being usedвЂ”`AHV_API_KEY` vs `AHVHOLDING_API_KEY`вЂ”that could cause the credentials to come back empty.","thinkingSignature":"31d5fce9dec758aa885054bd7d9df0448878c3ca338d647c46f1efb2a973b655"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_pgvplq81s1ci_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"sed -n '408,470p' /root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/ahv-openclaw-setup/bin/ahv-setup.js"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":203,"output":269,"cacheRead":61305,"cacheWrite":1411,"totalTokens":63188,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776304507774,"responseId":"062f747df37be24a0cd4717a8c1635f7"}}
{"type":"message","id":"c41b0964","parentId":"2d9f36fb","timestamp":"2026-04-16T01:55:16.055Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_pgvplq81s1ci_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"const args = process.argv.slice(2);\n  let team = null, skipIntro = false;\n  for (const arg of args) {\n    if (arg === \"--team\" || arg === \"-t\") {\n      const idx = args.indexOf(arg);\n      team = args[idx + 1];\n    }\n    if (arg.startsWith(\"--team=\")) team = arg.replace(\"--team=\", \"\");\n    if (arg === \"--yes\" || arg === \"-y\") skipIntro = true;\n  }\n\n  checkPrereqs();\n\n  if (!team) {\n    if (skipIntro) { team = \"dev\"; }\n    else {\n      const { selected } = await inquirer.prompt([{\n        type: \"list\", name: \"selected\", message: chalk.cyan(\"Chon team:\"),\n        choices: [\n          { name: \"рџ‘Ёрџ’» Team Dev  вЂ” Backend, Frontend, DevOps\", value: \"dev\" },\n          { name: \"рџ“Љ Team BA   вЂ” Product Owner, Strategy, Epic Design\", value: \"ba\" },\n          { name: \"рџ§Є Team QA  вЂ” QA, Playwright, Security, Performance\", value: \"qa\" }\n        ]\n      }]);\n      team = selected;\n    }\n  }\n\n  if (!TEAMS[team]) { console.log(chalk.red(`\\nвќЊ Team khong hop le: ${team}\\n`)); process.exit(1); }\n\n  console.log(chalk.bold(`\\nв–¶ ${TEAMS[team].name} вЂ” ${TEAMS[team].desc}`));\n  console.log(chalk.dim(`   Agents: ${TEAMS[team].agents.length} | MCP: ${TEAMS[team].mcp.join(\", \")}\\n`));\n\n  if (!skipIntro) {\n    const { confirm } = await inquirer.prompt([{\n      type: \"confirm\", name: \"confirm\", message: chalk.cyan(\"Tiep tuc cai dat?\"), default: true\n    }]);\n    if (!confirm) { console.log(chalk.dim(\"\\nDa huy.\\n\")); process.exit(0); }\n  }\n\n  let config = loadTemplate(team);\n  console.log(chalk.bold(chalk.underline(\"\\nрџ”ђ Nhap credentials\\n\")));\n  const answers = await collectCredentials(team);\n  config = applyCredentials(config, answers);\n\n  console.log(chalk.bold(\"\\nрџ“¦ Tom tat:\\n\"));\n  console.log(`  ${chalk.green(\"вњ“\")} Team: ${TEAMS[team].name}`);\n  console.log(`  ${chalk.green(\"вњ“\")} Agents: ${TEAMS[team].agents.length}`);\n  console.log(`  ${chalk.green(\"вњ“\")} MCP: ${TEAMS[team].mcp.join(\", \")}`);\n\n  const { write } = await inquirer.prompt([{\n    type: \"confirm\", name: \"write\",\n    message: chalk.cyan(\"\\nGhi config vao ~/.openclaw/openclaw.json?\"), default: true\n  }]);\n  if (!write) { console.log(chalk.dim(\"\\nDa huy.\\n\")); process.exit(0); }\n\n  const homePath = (answers.openclawPath || \"$HOME/.openclaw\").replace(/^\\$HOME/, process.env.HOME || \"\");\n  applyConfig(config, answers, team);\n  restartGateway();\n\n  console.log(chalk.bold(chalk.green(\"\\nвњ… Setup hoan tat!\\n\")));\n  console.log(chalk.dim(`  вЂў Config + workspaces: ${homePath}`));\n  console.log(chalk.dim(`  вЂў Skills: ${homePath}/skills/`));"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":54,"aggregated":"const args = process.argv.slice(2);\n  let team = null, skipIntro = false;\n  for (const arg of args) {\n    if (arg === \"--team\" || arg === \"-t\") {\n      const idx = args.indexOf(arg);\n      team = args[idx + 1];\n    }\n    if (arg.startsWith(\"--team=\")) team = arg.replace(\"--team=\", \"\");\n    if (arg === \"--yes\" || arg === \"-y\") skipIntro = true;\n  }\n\n  checkPrereqs();\n\n  if (!team) {\n    if (skipIntro) { team = \"dev\"; }\n    else {\n      const { selected } = await inquirer.prompt([{\n        type: \"list\", name: \"selected\", message: chalk.cyan(\"Chon team:\"),\n        choices: [\n          { name: \"рџ‘Ёрџ’» Team Dev  вЂ” Backend, Frontend, DevOps\", value: \"dev\" },\n          { name: \"рџ“Љ Team BA   вЂ” Product Owner, Strategy, Epic Design\", value: \"ba\" },\n          { name: \"рџ§Є Team QA  вЂ” QA, Playwright, Security, Performance\", value: \"qa\" }\n        ]\n      }]);\n      team = selected;\n    }\n  }\n\n  if (!TEAMS[team]) { console.log(chalk.red(`\\nвќЊ Team khong hop le: ${team}\\n`)); process.exit(1); }\n\n  console.log(chalk.bold(`\\nв–¶ ${TEAMS[team].name} вЂ” ${TEAMS[team].desc}`));\n  console.log(chalk.dim(`   Agents: ${TEAMS[team].agents.length} | MCP: ${TEAMS[team].mcp.join(\", \")}\\n`));\n\n  if (!skipIntro) {\n    const { confirm } = await inquirer.prompt([{\n      type: \"confirm\", name: \"confirm\", message: chalk.cyan(\"Tiep tuc cai dat?\"), default: true\n    }]);\n    if (!confirm) { console.log(chalk.dim(\"\\nDa huy.\\n\")); process.exit(0); }\n  }\n\n  let config = loadTemplate(team);\n  console.log(chalk.bold(chalk.underline(\"\\nрџ”ђ Nhap credentials\\n\")));\n  const answers = await collectCredentials(team);\n  config = applyCredentials(config, answers);\n\n  console.log(chalk.bold(\"\\nрџ“¦ Tom tat:\\n\"));\n  console.log(`  ${chalk.green(\"вњ“\")} Team: ${TEAMS[team].name}`);\n  console.log(`  ${chalk.green(\"вњ“\")} Agents: ${TEAMS[team].agents.length}`);\n  console.log(`  ${chalk.green(\"вњ“\")} MCP: ${TEAMS[team].mcp.join(\", \")}`);\n\n  const { write } = await inquirer.prompt([{\n    type: \"confirm\", name: \"write\",\n    message: chalk.cyan(\"\\nGhi config vao ~/.openclaw/openclaw.json?\"), default: true\n  }]);\n  if (!write) { console.log(chalk.dim(\"\\nDa huy.\\n\")); process.exit(0); }\n\n  const homePath = (answers.openclawPath || \"$HOME/.openclaw\").replace(/^\\$HOME/, process.env.HOME || \"\");\n  applyConfig(config, answers, team);\n  restartGateway();\n\n  console.log(chalk.bold(chalk.green(\"\\nвњ… Setup hoan tat!\\n\")));\n  console.log(chalk.dim(`  вЂў Config + workspaces: ${homePath}`));\n  console.log(chalk.dim(`  вЂў Skills: ${homePath}/skills/`));","cwd":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776304515986}}
