{"type":"message","id":"a04787bb","parentId":"d625aea8","timestamp":"2026-04-16T03:05:22.455Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good, the team configs look correct. Now let me update the install script to:\n1. NOT overwrite existing `~/.openclaw/openclaw.json`\n2. Instead, just copy the generated config to `~/.openclaw/openclaw.generated-{team}.json`\n3. Or prompt user if they want to overwrite\n\nActually, let me think about what the setup script should do:\n- The user runs `curl | bash` which clones the repo and runs `ahv-setup.js`\n- `ahv-setup.js` should:\n  1. NOT overwrite existing `~/.openclaw/openclaw.json`\n  2. Generate the config based on the team\n  3. Save it as a new file (e.g., `~/.openclaw/openclaw.generated-{team}.json`)\n  4. Tell the user to manually merge or use it\n\nThe best approach is to check if `openclaw.json` already exists and skip the write step entirely, just show the user what was generated. I need to find where `ahv-setup.js` writes the config and update it to either prompt for permission or save to a different filename instead of overwriting.","thinkingSignature":"f006fd121d0bc72d20c375b27c9627b0c08ae1c669150d62e5ffc1ad32ecd2df"},{"type":"text","text":"Configs Д‘Гєng rб»“i. Giб»ќ sб»­a installer вЂ” **khГґng bao giб»ќ overwrite `openclaw.json` hiб»‡n cГі**:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_hlelm1at1d09_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -n \"applyConfig\\|restartGateway\\|write.*config\\|openclaw.json\" /root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/ahv-openclaw-setup/bin/ahv-setup.js | head -15"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":657,"output":345,"cacheRead":99311,"cacheWrite":2228,"totalTokens":102541,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776308709234,"responseId":"062f84e75ba0784b6a5a7befa6b7fc1f"}}
