{"type":"message","id":"8ba9d41a","parentId":"741817c6","timestamp":"2026-04-16T03:09:15.347Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_s8hsqtw7t8ev_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"// в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ Apply credentials to config в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ\nfunction applyCredentials(config, answers) {\n  // Build replacement map from answers\n  const vars = {\n    AHVHOLDING_API_KEY:  answers.ahvApiKey,\n    GITLAB_TOKEN:        answers.gitlabToken,\n    CONFLUENCE_URL:      answers.confUrl,\n    CONFLUENCE_EMAIL:    answers.confEmail,\n    CONFLUENCE_TOKEN:   answers.confToken,\n    STITCH_API_KEY:      answers.stitchKey,\n  };\n\n  // Replace all {{...}} placeholders recursively\n  const replaced = replacePlaceholders(config, vars);\n\n  // Also update channels.telegram.accounts.main_bot.botToken if telegramBot provided\n  if (answers.telegramBot) {\n    const accounts = replaced.channels?.telegram?.accounts || {};\n    for (const key of Object.keys(accounts)) {\n      if (answers.telegramBot) {\n        accounts[key].botToken = answers.telegramBot;"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":78,"aggregated":"// в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ Apply credentials to config в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ\nfunction applyCredentials(config, answers) {\n  // Build replacement map from answers\n  const vars = {\n    AHVHOLDING_API_KEY:  answers.ahvApiKey,\n    GITLAB_TOKEN:        answers.gitlabToken,\n    CONFLUENCE_URL:      answers.confUrl,\n    CONFLUENCE_EMAIL:    answers.confEmail,\n    CONFLUENCE_TOKEN:   answers.confToken,\n    STITCH_API_KEY:      answers.stitchKey,\n  };\n\n  // Replace all {{...}} placeholders recursively\n  const replaced = replacePlaceholders(config, vars);\n\n  // Also update channels.telegram.accounts.main_bot.botToken if telegramBot provided\n  if (answers.telegramBot) {\n    const accounts = replaced.channels?.telegram?.accounts || {};\n    for (const key of Object.keys(accounts)) {\n      if (answers.telegramBot) {\n        accounts[key].botToken = answers.telegramBot;","cwd":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776308955270}}
{"type":"message","id":"265a98a5","parentId":"8ba9d41a","timestamp":"2026-04-16T03:09:27.241Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The `applyCredentials` function replaces `{{VAR}}` patterns with values from `vars`. It handles:\n- `AHVHOLDING_API_KEY`\n- `GITLAB_TOKEN`\n- `CONFLUENCE_URL` (but our config uses `CONFLUENCE_BASE_URL`)\n- `CONFLUENCE_EMAIL`\n- `CONFLUENCE_TOKEN`\n- `STITCH_API_KEY`\n\nBut our generated configs use `{{CONFLUENCE_BASE_URL}}` and `{{GITLAB_URL}}` while `applyCredentials` only handles `CONFLUENCE_URL`. I need to update the vars map in `applyCredentials` to include `CONFLUENCE_BASE_URL` and `GITLAB_URL`.","thinkingSignature":"929be06df8893327036dc580bb20b0e51f8978225ebee1a16f470f900ec6587b"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_8v7pycnc9afa_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/ahv-openclaw-setup && python3 - << 'PYEOF'\nwith open('bin/ahv-setup.js', 'rb') as f:\n    raw = f.read()\n\n# Fix applyCredentials vars map to include CONFLUENCE_BASE_URL and GITLAB_URL\nold_vars = b'''const vars = {\n    AHVHOLDING_API_KEY:  answers.ahvApiKey,\n    GITLAB_TOKEN:        answers.gitlabToken,\n    CONFLUENCE_URL:      answers.confUrl,\n    CONFLUENCE_EMAIL:    answers.confEmail,\n    CONFLUENCE_TOKEN:   answers.confToken,\n    STITCH_API_KEY:      answers.stitchKey,\n  };'''\n\nnew_vars = b'''const vars = {\n    AHVHOLDING_API_KEY:   answers.ahvApiKey,\n    GITLAB_TOKEN:         answers.gitlabToken,\n    GITLAB_URL:           answers.gitlabUrl,\n    CONFLUENCE_BASE_URL:  answers.confUrl,\n    CONFLUENCE_USERNAME:  answers.confEmail,\n    CONFLUENCE_TOKEN:     answers.confToken,\n    STITCH_API_KEY:       answers.stitchKey,\n    TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN:   answers.telegramBot,\n  };'''\n\nif old_vars in raw:\n    raw = raw.replace(old_vars, new_vars)\n    print('вњ… vars map updated')\nelse:\n    print('вќЊ vars not found')\n\nwith open('bin/ahv-setup.js', 'wb') as f:\n    f.write(raw)\nPYEOF"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":346,"output":503,"cacheRead":111461,"cacheWrite":2560,"totalTokens":114870,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776308955357,"responseId":"062f85dd05d1d44ae1b49f8f9d83fd25"}}
