{"type":"message","id":"4d40590e","parentId":"54923779","timestamp":"2026-04-16T03:12:33.275Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The configs look correct. The issue might be that the `bin/ahv-setup.js` was already compiled from the local version, but the `loadTemplate` function was using a different approach. Let me look at what the actual loadTemplate function does in the current state of the file.","thinkingSignature":"15827951380a8bbec585afdca59c8729d3e18c37d0c7408f562141d72c35bc67"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_zyotgk318inn_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"sed -n '167,210p' /root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/ahv-openclaw-setup/bin/ahv-setup.js"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":270,"output":119,"cacheRead":121894,"cacheWrite":963,"totalTokens":123246,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776309146653,"responseId":"062f869ca2880354ebf6e3ced3855bc8"}}
{"type":"message","id":"d395b8c0","parentId":"4d40590e","timestamp":"2026-04-16T03:12:33.523Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_zyotgk318inn_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"function loadTemplate(team) {\n  // 1. Load full base config (34 agents, gateway, channels, bindings, mcp)\n  const fullPath = path.join(__dirname, \"..\", \"configs\", \"openclaw-full.json\");\n  if (!fs.existsSync(fullPath)) {\n    console.log(chalk.red(`\\nвќЊ Full config not found: ${fullPath}`)); process.exit(1);\n  }\n  const base = JSON.parse(fs.readFileSync(fullPath, \"utf8\"));\n\n  // 2. Load team config for agent list + name/description\n  const teamPath = getConfigPath(team);\n  if (!fs.existsSync(teamPath)) { console.log(chalk.red(`\\nвќЊ Team config not found: ${teamPath}`)); process.exit(1); }\n  const teamCfg = JSON.parse(fs.readFileSync(teamPath, \"utf8\"));\n\n  // 3. Override name/description\n  base.name = teamCfg.name || base.name;\n  base.description = teamCfg.description || base.description;\n\n  // 4. Filter agents.list to only this team's agents\n  const teamAgents = new Set(teamCfg.agents || []);\n  base.agents.list = (base.agents.list || []).filter(a => teamAgents.has(a.id));\n\n  // 5. Filter bindings to only this team's agents\n  const masterAgents = new Set([\"master-orchestrator\", \"prompt-optimizer\", ...(teamCfg.agents || [])]);\n  base.bindings = (base.bindings || []).filter(b => masterAgents.has(b.agentId));\n\n  // 6. Override defaults.workspace and defaults.skills\n  base.agents.defaults.workspace = \"{{AGENT_HOME}}/workspace\";\n  base.agents.defaults.skills = [\"{{AGENT_HOME}}/skills\"];\n\n  return base;\n}\n\n// в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ Build answers from env vars (pipe/non-TTY mode) в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ\nfunction buildAnswersFromEnv(team) {\n  const required = REQUIRED_CREDS[team] || [];\n  const answers = { openclawPath: process.env.OPENCLAW_HOME || \"$HOME/.openclaw\" };\n\n  for (const cred of required) {\n    switch (cred) {\n      case \"AHV_API_KEY\":\n        answers.ahvApiKey = process.env.AHVHOLDING_API_KEY || \"\";\n        break;\n      case \"GITLAB_TOKEN\":\n        answers.gitlabToken = process.env.GITLAB_TOKEN || \"\";"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":72,"aggregated":"function loadTemplate(team) {\n  // 1. Load full base config (34 agents, gateway, channels, bindings, mcp)\n  const fullPath = path.join(__dirname, \"..\", \"configs\", \"openclaw-full.json\");\n  if (!fs.existsSync(fullPath)) {\n    console.log(chalk.red(`\\nвќЊ Full config not found: ${fullPath}`)); process.exit(1);\n  }\n  const base = JSON.parse(fs.readFileSync(fullPath, \"utf8\"));\n\n  // 2. Load team config for agent list + name/description\n  const teamPath = getConfigPath(team);\n  if (!fs.existsSync(teamPath)) { console.log(chalk.red(`\\nвќЊ Team config not found: ${teamPath}`)); process.exit(1); }\n  const teamCfg = JSON.parse(fs.readFileSync(teamPath, \"utf8\"));\n\n  // 3. Override name/description\n  base.name = teamCfg.name || base.name;\n  base.description = teamCfg.description || base.description;\n\n  // 4. Filter agents.list to only this team's agents\n  const teamAgents = new Set(teamCfg.agents || []);\n  base.agents.list = (base.agents.list || []).filter(a => teamAgents.has(a.id));\n\n  // 5. Filter bindings to only this team's agents\n  const masterAgents = new Set([\"master-orchestrator\", \"prompt-optimizer\", ...(teamCfg.agents || [])]);\n  base.bindings = (base.bindings || []).filter(b => masterAgents.has(b.agentId));\n\n  // 6. Override defaults.workspace and defaults.skills\n  base.agents.defaults.workspace = \"{{AGENT_HOME}}/workspace\";\n  base.agents.defaults.skills = [\"{{AGENT_HOME}}/skills\"];\n\n  return base;\n}\n\n// в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ Build answers from env vars (pipe/non-TTY mode) в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ\nfunction buildAnswersFromEnv(team) {\n  const required = REQUIRED_CREDS[team] || [];\n  const answers = { openclawPath: process.env.OPENCLAW_HOME || \"$HOME/.openclaw\" };\n\n  for (const cred of required) {\n    switch (cred) {\n      case \"AHV_API_KEY\":\n        answers.ahvApiKey = process.env.AHVHOLDING_API_KEY || \"\";\n        break;\n      case \"GITLAB_TOKEN\":\n        answers.gitlabToken = process.env.GITLAB_TOKEN || \"\";","cwd":"/root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/master-orchestrator"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776309153459}}
{"type":"message","id":"320e620d","parentId":"d395b8c0","timestamp":"2026-04-16T03:12:54.530Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see the issue now! The `loadTemplate` function filters `base.agents.list` by `teamAgents.has(a.id)`. But `teamAgents` is built from `new Set(teamCfg.agents || [])`. This means `teamCfg.agents` should be a list of agent IDs.\n\nBut in our generated `team-dev.json`, the `agents` field is NOT in the root - it's in the `agents.defaults.subagents.allowAgents` section! Looking at the generated config, we have:```json\n{\n  \"agents\": {\n    \"defaults\": {\n      \"subagents\": {\n        \"allowAgents\": [\"senior-backend\", ...]\n      }\n    },\n    \"list\": [...]\n  }\n}\n```The `loadTemplate` function expects `teamCfg.agents` to be a list of agent IDs (like `[\"senior-backend\", \"senior-frontend\", ...]`), but our generated config has `teamCfg.agents` as an object with `defaults` and `list` sub-objects!\n\nSo `new Set({...})` would fail because you can't create a Set from an object directly. Actually wait - in JavaScript, `new Set({...})` would just create an empty set because when you iterate over an object, you get its keys. So `new Set({a:1, b:2})` creates a Set with `[\"a\", \"b\"]`. But that's not what we want.\n\nThe real issue is that `teamCfg.agents || []` returns the `agents` object itself when it's present, and `new Set(agentsObject)` ends up iterating over the object keys instead of treating it as an array of agent IDs. Then when `filter` tries to check if `teamAgents.has(a.id)`, it's searching through those keys rather than the actual agent list, so nothing matches. This worked before with the original configs because they had `agents` as a simple array of IDs at the root level, but our new structure nests it deeper.","thinkingSignature":"db633e7e12a50f580ba4807e41745e92b520841f68e92e54d1d34a313a230f1a"},{"type":"text","text":"Bug: `teamCfg.agents` trong config mб»›i lГ  object, khГґng phбєЈi array. Fix:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_wh63ubliwj9x_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /root/.openclaw/workspaces2/v4-ecosystem-review/ahv-openclaw-setup && python3 - << 'PYEOF'\nwith open('bin/ahv-setup.js', 'r') as f:\n    content = f.read()\n\nold_filter = '''  // 4. Filter agents.list to only this team's agents\n  const teamAgents = new Set(teamCfg.agents || []);\n  base.agents.list = (base.agents.list || []).filter(a => teamAgents.has(a.id));\n\n  // 5. Filter bindings to only this team's agents\n  const masterAgents = new Set([\"master-orchestrator\", \"prompt-optimizer\", ...(teamCfg.agents || [])]);'''\n\nnew_filter = '''  // 4. Filter agents.list to only this team's agents\n  const teamAgentIds = Array.isArray(teamCfg.agents) ? teamCfg.agents\n    : (teamCfg.agents?.defaults?.subagents?.allowAgents || []);\n  const teamAgents = new Set(teamAgentIds);\n  base.agents.list = (base.agents.list || []).filter(a => teamAgents.has(a.id));\n\n  // 5. Filter bindings to only this team's agents\n  const masterAgents = new Set([\"master-orchestrator\",\"prompt-optimizer\", ...teamAgentIds]);'''\n\nif old_filter in content:\n    content = content.replace(old_filter, new_filter)\n    print('вњ… filter updated')\nelse:\n    print('вќЊ not found')\n\nwith open('bin/ahv-setup.js', 'w') as f:\n    f.write(content)\nPYEOF"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":653,"output":793,"cacheRead":122359,"cacheWrite":762,"totalTokens":124567,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776309153533,"responseId":"062f86a334f3ee058e74cb4517d00cb0"}}
