{"type":"message","id":"8d0550d2","parentId":"56302af8","timestamp":"2026-04-16T03:16:11.898Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Still the old version! The pull didn't update the file. Let me check what the install.sh actually ran.\n\nActually, looking at the install.sh more carefully:\n```bash\nif [ -d \"$INSTALL_DIR/.git\" ]; then\n    cd \"$INSTALL_DIR\" && git pull origin feat/full-setup-mcp --quiet\n```\n\nBut the install script was already running and used the OLD install.sh from the previous clone! The install script pulls using the `install.sh` that's already been read (cached). Or... actually no, the `git pull` is inside the install script which was downloaded fresh.\n\nWait - but the error is still happening. \n\nThe install script downloads fresh and clones the repo, then pulls from `feat/full-setup-mcp`. After the pull completes, I need to verify whether the pull actually succeeded or if there's an issue with the git operation itselfвЂ”maybe the curl download failed silently and we're still running an old version.","thinkingSignature":"851e7363e50addfce4fd36ebac94aa06aa10ecb558065ba3930dceb467f45283"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_v7256ow9bt7s_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /root/.openclaw-setup && git log --oneline -3 && echo \"---\" && grep -n \"teamAgentIds\\|teamAgents\" bin/ahv-setup.js | head -3"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"ahvholding","model":"AHV-Holding-DEV","usage":{"input":181,"output":258,"cacheRead":130006,"cacheWrite":644,"totalTokens":131089,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776309359309,"responseId":"062f8770e290c842dcf1625526fdcef4"}}
